f use.</div><div><br></div><div>On the other hand, we've got balm cleansers.&nbsp; &nbsp;Instead of a liquid, they're more like a solid, almost like a luxurious wax. Imagine a luxurious, creamy substance that glides smoothly onto your skin. It's like giving your face a gentle massage while effectively removing makeup and impurities.</div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1711459314451" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1711459314451" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1706278098343" data-id="1706278098343"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1711459314324" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1711459314324"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Water-Based Cleanser</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1711459314442" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1711459314442"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The second step of the double cleansing is a water-based cleanser. Water cleansers are used to remove water-based impurities like sweat and dirt after your oil cleanser removes oil-based impurities like makeup and SPF. Go for a gentle cleanser that cleanses effectively</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1711459314375" class="gf_row gf_equal-height" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1711459314375" data-layout-lg="8+4" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="8+4" data-layout-sm="12+12" data-layout-xs="12+12" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; visibility: visible;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-8 gf_col-md-8 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1707204262536" data-id="1707204262536" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1711459314418" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1711459314418"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">some cleansers can be a bit harsh and leave your skin feeling dry.&nbsp; Not all cleansers are like that! We're all about the water-based ones that not only clean but also keep your skin hydrated and balanced.&nbsp; We recommend going for water-based cleansers with a low pH, around 5.5. Why, you ask? Because that's like the sweet spot that matches your skin's natural acidity.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Using a low pH cleanser isn't just about getting rid of impurities; it's about maintaining that happy place for your skin. So, if you've ever worried about your cleanser being too harsh, dive into the world of water-based cleansers with us. Your skin will thank you for the hydrating and balancing functions they bring to the skincare table!</div></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-4 gf_col-md-4 gf_col-xs-12 gf_col-sm-12" id="c-1707204264629" data-id="1707204264629" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; min-height: auto;"><div data-label="Product" data-key="product" data-atomgroup="product" id="m-1711459314371" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-product" data-ver="3.1" data-id="1711459314371" data-assigned-ver="4" style="min-height: auto; display: block;"><div class="module" data-variant="auto" style="" data-current-variant="39724021416065"><product-form class="product-form">{% assign product = all_pr